<div id="review_3709642617" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3709642617" />
    <a title="Tatyana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57432097-tatyana"><img alt="Tatyana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1538736056p2/57432097.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3709642617?book_show_action=true">Dec 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tatyana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tatyana" href="/user/show/57432097-tatyana">Tatyana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/57432097-tatyana?shelf=memoirs">memoirs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3709642617" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8816625202069439980">&quot;This damn year is finally over. But what will be next ? Perhaps things will get worse. And that seems even likely.&quot;<br/><br/>&quot;This is the hellish secret of the Bolsheviks—to kill all sensitivity. People live as best they can; their sensitivity and their imagination have been taken away from them, for the people have crossed the fatal line. Take the price of bread or beef, for example. “What ? Three rubles a pound !” Then it goes up to a thousand—but there comes an end to the shock and screaming; stupor a</span>
  <span id="freeText8816625202069439980" style="display:none">"This damn year is finally over. But what will be next ? Perhaps things will get worse. And that seems even likely."<br /><br />"This is the hellish secret of the Bolsheviks—to kill all sensitivity. People live as best they can; their sensitivity and their imagination have been taken away from them, for the people have crossed the fatal line. Take the price of bread or beef, for example. “What ? Three rubles a pound !” Then it goes up to a thousand—but there comes an end to the shock and screaming; stupor and passivity take their place. “What ? Seven were hanged ?!” “No, my dear, not seven, but seven hundred !” Already you are stunned beyond measure—you can still imagine seven being hanged, but try to imagine seven hundred, even seventy ! . . ."<br /><br />"At night I am plagued by anxious dreams about trains and seas and very pretty<br />landscapes, but they leave me morbid and sad—and tensely expecting something. . . ."<br /><br />"When I go out, I feel as though I’m on the verge of getting seriously ill."<br /><br />"One of the most distinguishing features of a revolution is the ravenous hunger for histrionics, dissembling, posturing, and puppet show. The ape has awakened in man."<br /><br />"There is so much lying going around that I could suffocate. All my friends, all my acquaintances, people whom earlier I never would have thought of as liars, are now uttering falsehoods at every turn. They cannot help but lie; they cannot help but add to their own lies, their own flourishes to well-known falsehoods. And they all do so from an agonizing need that everything be just as they so fiercely desire. They rave on like they have a fever; and when I hear their rantings I take their words in greedily and become infected by them. Otherwise it seems that I won’t survive the week."<br /><br />"Gruzinsky said: “With every fiber of my being, I now avoid going out on the street unless I really have to. And not at all from fear that someone is going to mug me, but merely because of the faces that I see out there now.”<br />I understand him like never before, for I also experience the same thing, only, I think, still more sharply."<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8816625202069439980" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


